cs.DS, cs.GT, cs.LG, cs.NA, cs.OC 

The paper deals with online optimization problems, specifically covering problems with convex objectives. This makes it likely to belong to the categories of cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms), cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory), cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.NA (Numerical Analysis), and cs.OC (Optimization and Control). The paper uses algorithmic frameworks and techniques from these areas to solve the problem of minimizing general convex objectives over a set of covering constraints that arrive online.
